THE CFI WAS GIVING RECURRENT INSTRUCTION TO A LICENSED PILOT IN SEA 
PLANE OPERATIONS. HE SAID THAT THEY TOUCHED DOWN TOO CLOSE TO THE 
SHORELINE, AND THAT HE (THE CFI) WAS UNABLE TO STOP THE AIRPLANE OR 
MANEUVER IT AWAY FROM THE SHORE BEFORE STRIKING TREES. 
THE CFI'S FAILURE TO TAKE TIMELY ACTION WHEN THE DUAL STUDENT DID NOT 
ATTAIN A PROPER TOUCH DOWN POINT. 
